organic_results.title: Schooling Taiwan's women: Educational attainment in the mid-20th century
organic_results.snippet: This article presents a study of the impact of educational expansion on the equality of educational opportunity for men and women in Taiwan. The study found that as the average level of schooling increased during the 45 years covered by the data, severe limitations on females' access to education remained and occurred as early as the compulsory level. Marked ethnic differences appeared in the middle of the educational hierarchy, as did inequalities of educational opportunity that were due to father's occupational class. Among …
